  "Has no time": [
   {
    "text": "A word in the participle of Hebrew or Aramaic does not alone tell us what time the action happened. This is like the English word “running,” which only describes an action, not when it happened. We require the context of the sentence to determine the time of the action.",
    "type": "text"
   }
  ],
  "In the past": [
   {
    "text": "The participle can be used in the past tense, for example הוא היה כותב, ",
    "type": "text"
